Surprisingly bad explanation of how the song is not ironic, since it only includes a definition of "verbal irony." I agree that most of the lyrics are not ironic, but this explanation is terrible. I can't believe this article has been cited as exemplary.  <span style="font-size: smaller;" class="autosigned">— Preceding [[Wikipedia:Signatures|unsigned]] comment added by [[Special:Contributions/65.69.204.131|65.69.204.131]] ([[User talk:65.69.204.131|talk]]) 15:14, 15 April 2014 (UTC)</span><!-- Template:Unsigned IP --> <!--Autosigned by SineBot-->

== Weird Al parody ==

I remember watching Al Music in '96 as a teenager obsessed with modern music and he definitely parodied the Ironic video then, not in 2003. This is easily supported by the fact that in the parody, he has his signature glasses and moustache style and not the later clean shaven/contacts look he adopted in '99.  <small><span class="autosigned">—&nbsp;Preceding [[Wikipedia:Signatures|unsigned]] comment added by [[User:Moe45673|Moe45673]] ([[User talk:Moe45673|talk]] • [[Special:Contributions/Moe45673|contribs]]) 14:55, 31 March 2016 (UTC)</span></small><!-- Template:Unsigned --> <!--Autosigned by SineBot-->
